{{Infobox company | name = Illustria | logo = Illustrialogo.png | type = Private | foundation = 2013 | location = [[Washington, D.C.]] | industry = Design | key_people = Katherine Long (Founder & CEO) | services = [[Graphic design]] (web, digital, UI/UX, print, infographics, branding) | homepage = [http://www.illustriadesigns.com/ www.illustriadesigns.com] }}
'''Illustria''' is a branding agency that provides design services (web, digital, UI/UX, print, infographics). Their mission is to make the agency experience transparent, inclusive, and accountable.
==History== While the founders were working on a previous start-up, they found it difficult to find professional and accessible design services. Illustria came about as a way to provide these services to others.
Founder & CEO, Katherine Long initially believed that only small businesses would be interested in the company's services, but after calling multiple companies<ref>http://articles.bplans.com/you-have-an-idea-for-a-business-now-what/</ref> found that even larger businesses experienced the same types of pain that could be solved by Illustria's business model.
==Services== Illustria is a branding agency based in Washington, DC that uses an objective branding process to ensure that they enable you to tell your story accurately. With brand strategy at the center, Illustria's capabilities extend to UI/UX website & application design, general graphic design, and development. Illustria follows a unique set of five methods to guide their process: Nothing Surface Level, Open & Honest Communication, Members, Not Clients, Dedicated Team, and Zero Big Reveals.
==Reception== Illustria has worked with companies like the [[WWE]], [[Hubspot]], [[XEROX Parc]] and more. The company has received reviews that praise their [[turnaround time]] as well as the designs that they have provided.
